text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia retrorsa is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Mid West regions of Western Australia.The spreading prostrate shrub typically grows to a height of 0.05 to 0.5 metres (0 to 2 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
